The paper deals with the achievability of the Cramer-Rao bound in noisy compressed sensing, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also involves the use of concentration of measures inequality, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper involves the use of typical estimator, which is a concept in multimedia (cs.MM).
